sql:
SELECT AVG(sm.coef) AS average_coefficient
FROM statistical_measures sm
WHERE sm.p_value_t < 0.05;

external_knowledge:
- A p-value less than 0.05 is commonly used in scientific research to indicate statistical significance, suggesting that the observed results are unlikely due to chance alone;
- Rejecting the null hypothesis means that there is enough evidence to support the alternative hypothesis;
- A sample size of more than 100 participants is often considered sufficiently large to ensure the reliability of the statistical analysis.

